        <section id="distro" class="third-section">
            <h1>Distributed & Network Operating Systems</h1>
            <div class="main-area">
                <div class="main-area-left"></div>
                <div class="main-area-center">
                    <h2 class="bigger-font">Distributed Operating System</h2>
                    <p>A Distributed OS manages multiple connected computers and makes them function as one system.</p>
                    <h3>Characteristics:</h3>
                    <ul class="no-margin">
                        <li>Shared resources</li>
                        <li>Improved reliability</li>
                        <li>Used in cloud and cluster systems</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h2 class="bigger-font padding-top">Network Operating System (NOS)</h2>
                    <p>A Network OS manages and controls resources across a network.</p>
                    <h3>Characteristics:</h3>
                    <ul class="no-margin">
                        <li>File and printer sharing</li>
                        <li>Centralized user management</li>
                        <li>Server-based control</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Example: </strong>Windows Server, Linux Server.</p>
                </div>
