        <section class="fourth-section" id="rtos">
            <h1>Real-Time Operating Systems (RTOS)</h1>
            <div class="main-area">
                <div class="main-area-left"></div>
                <div class="main-area-center">
                    <p>A Real-Time Operating System is designed to process data within strict time limits.</p>
                    <h2>Types:</h2>
                    <ul class="no-margin">
                        <li>Hard Real-Time: Deadlines must be met exactly</li>
                        <li>Soft Real-Time: Small delays are acceptable</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h2 class="padding-top">Examples:</h2>
                    <ul class="no-margin">
                        <li>Medical devices</li>
                        <li>Industrial control systems</li>
                        <li>Air traffic control</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Why it matters: </strong>RTOS systems are used where timing and reliability are critical.</p>
                    <p class="no-margin small-text">
